en_497371_0	10 (V) Vijayabahu Infantry Regiment (VIR) troops of the Security Force Headquarters - Jaffna (SFHQ-J) on account of their 24th anniversary launched a blood donation camp for the benefit of patients at the Jaffna Teaching Hospital on Thursday (24) at their battalion Headquarters premises in Maradankerni.
en_497371_1	A total of 102 Army personnel including Officers and Other Ranks of the 10 VIR troops volunteered to donate blood during the mobile campaign.
en_497371_2	The doctors and medical team of the Jaffna Reaching Hospital thanked the Army for its timely gesture.
